us, Tat, I don''t know!" Possibly that''s a bit of an overreaction, but she looks more amused than upset. "All right, all right...." She gets a mischievous look in her eyes.', 6944, 0), (308723, 'God is after the bigger picture of your life. He is writing your story. I''m about to say something that may seem antithetical to this book, but need you to hear this: your story has far more to do with finding God''s unique calling and purpose for your life than it does with finding the love of your life.', 22457, 0), (308724, 'He looks good for a while, but ya know, ya can’t shine a sneaker.', 35661, 0), (308725, 'I recently heard a talk about identity in which the speaker said it''s almost as though we are born into a world in which we are constantly being labeled by others -- our parents, our friends, our family, and people we don''t even know. Each person, from the outside looking in, comes up with a label to slap onto us without our permission. Some labels are kind and some are truthful, but many of them are lies. And sometimes we leave the negative labels on so long that we believe what they say; we allow those labels to define us.', 22457, 0), (308726, 'Girlfriends aren’t allowed to care if you have Stilton socks. Friends are.” All the same, she gave her hands a quick, professional shake and took hold of my foot. “Plus, you might be less of a pain in the arse if you got more action.', 546, 0), (308727, 'The remnants of his adolescent vulnerability were all over his face.', 35661, 0), (308728, 'You never know what you''re going to get with a pinball game," John said. "It''s a lot like life. You can''t control it, so you have to just roll with it and do the best you can. And if you do well enough, sometimes you get a bonus play.', 35661, 0), (308729, 'The most difficult part of dating as a single parent is deciding how much risk your own child’s heart is worth.', 645, 0), (308730, 'Sometimes a girl needs to be told what a guy feels, rather than trying to decipher the 